casebody.data:
Lamberto Lucarelli v. Freedom of Information Commission et al. (11788)

O’Connell, Landau and Schaller, Js.

Argued September 28 decision released October 19, 1993 Lamberto Lucarelli, pro se, the appellant (plaintiff). Colleen M. Murphy, commission counsel, with whom were Ralph E. Urban, assistant attorney general, and, on the brief, Mitchell W. Pearlman, general counsel, for the appellee (named defendant). Per Curiam.

The judgment is affirmed.
